# Function to create boxplots for specified columns
create_boxplots <- function(data, columns) {
  for (col in columns) {
    print(ggplot(data, aes_string(x = "1", y = col)) + 
            geom_boxplot(fill = "skyblue", alpha = 0.7) +
            labs(title = paste("Boxplot of", col), x = "", y = col) +
            theme_minimal())
  }
}

# Columns to plot
columns <- c("NO", "NO2", "NOx", "NH3", "CO")

# Create boxplots
create_boxplots(data, columns)

# Assuming your dataset is loaded into a dataframe called 'data'

# Select the columns with numerical data types
num_cols <- data %>% 
  select(where(is.numeric)) %>% 
  names()

# Initialize a variable to store the cleaned data
new_data <- data

# Loop through each numerical column and remove outliers using IQR
for (col in num_cols) {
  q1 <- quantile(new_data[[col]], 0.25)
  q3 <- quantile(new_data[[col]], 0.75)
  iqr <- q3 - q1
  upper_limit <- q3 + (1.5 * iqr)
  lower_limit <- q1 - (1.5 * iqr)
  
  # Remove outliers
  new_data <- new_data %>% 
    filter(.data[[col]] <= upper_limit & .data[[col]] >= lower_limit)
  
  # Print the number of rows before and after removing outliers
  cat("Before removing outliers:", nrow(data), "\n")
  cat("After removing outliers:", nrow(new_data), "\n")
  cat("Outliers removed:", nrow(data) - nrow(new_data), "\n")
}

# Load necessary libraries
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)

# Convert Date column to Date type
data$Date <- as.Date(data$Date, format="%Y-%m-%d")

# Extract year from Date column
data$Year <- format(data$Date, "%Y")

# Calculate the average AQI for each city per year
yearly_aqi <- data %>%
  group_by(Year, City) %>%
  summarise(Average_AQI = mean(AQI, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  arrange(Year, desc(Average_AQI))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# Identify the city with the maximum AQI for each year
max_aqi_city <- yearly_aqi %>%
  group_by(Year) %>%
  slice_max(order_by = Average_AQI, n = 1)

# Print the results
print(max_aqi_city)

library(rpart)
library(randomForest)

library(caret)
## Warning: package 'caret' was built under R version 4.4.1
## Loading required package: lattice
# Define features and target
features <- data[, c('PM2.5', 'PM10', 'NO', 'NO2', 'NOx', 'NH3', 'CO', 'SO2', 'O3', 'Benzene', 'Toluene', 'Xylene')]
target <- data$AQI

# Split the data into training and testing sets
set.seed(42)
trainIndex <- createDataPartition(target, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
X_train <- features[trainIndex, ]
X_test <- features[-trainIndex, ]
y_train <- target[trainIndex]
y_test <- target[-trainIndex]

# Train Decision Tree model
dt_model <- rpart(y_train ~ ., data = as.data.frame(X_train), method = "anova")

# Predict and evaluate Decision Tree model
dt_predictions <- predict(dt_model, as.data.frame(X_test))
dt_mse <- mean((y_test - dt_predictions)^2)
dt_r2 <- 1 - sum((y_test - dt_predictions)^2) / sum((y_test - mean(y_test))^2)

cat("Decision Tree MSE:", dt_mse, "\n")
## Decision Tree MSE: 658.1577
cat("Decision Tree R:", dt_r2,"\n")
## Decision Tree R: 0.7404237

  # Train Random Forest model

rf_mse <- mean((y_test - rf_predictions)^2)
rf_r2 <- 1 - sum((y_test - rf_predictions)^2) / sum((y_test - mean(y_test))^2)
